Cell.Data: Sorry, the name %1 is already taken. Please chose another name.
Пробачте, ім'я %1 вже вибрано. Будьте ласкаві вибрати інше.
Are you sure you want to delete %1? All your items and progression will be lost.
Ви направду хочете видалити %1? Усі Ваші предмети та прогрес зникнуть.
You cannot have more than %1 active characters.
У Вас не може бути більш ніж %1 активних персонажів.
Your remaining Attributes Points. You earn them when gaining levels and can spend them between Ferocity, Toughness, Dexterity and Willpower.
Your current experience at this level. You can gain experience by killing monsters and achieving Quests. Reaching the experience cap will increase your Character level.
Your maximum Health Points. You lose them when enemies hit you, and die if they reach 0.
The amount of Health Points you restore each second.
Your total Ferocity. Affects your Melee Damage, Critical Damage, Defensive Ability and Attack Speed.
Your total Agility. Affects your Ranged Damage, Critical Chance, Dodge Chance and Movement Speed.
Your total Toughness. Affects your Maximum Health, Defense Regeneration, Stamina Regeneration and all your basic Resistances.
Your total Willpower. Affects your Spell Damage, Health Regeneration, Status Ailments Chance and your Spells Resistance.

Your total Defense capacity which shields the part of your Health pool that is within your Defense range. By default, Defense only protects from Physical attacks and is usually obtained through Armor parts and Shields.
Your total Defensive Ability. Represents the Damage reduction applied on incoming Physical attacks which affect the part of your Health that is within your Defense range.

The amount of Defense points you restore per second when your Defense is shattered by an external source (expressed in percentage of total Defense per second). Also increases the duration of temporary Defense boosts.
The average Damage you deal in one strike with your equipped Weapons.
The global modifier to your Attack Speed with all weapons and spells.
Your average Damage Rate with equipped weapons, given their Damage and Attack Speed.
The Damage modifier applied to your attacks with Magic Spells.
The Damage modifier applied to your attacks with Melee Weapons.
The Damage modifier applied to your attacks with Ranged Weapons.
The global modifier to your chance of inflicting any Status Ailment.
The global Speed modifier to your attacks with Magic Spells.
Your current Attack Speed with equipped Weapons.
The global Speed modifier to your attacks with Melee Weapons.
The global Speed modifier to your attacks with Ranged Weapons.
Your maximum available Resource, in both Umbra and Rage. Umbra and Rage are used to cast Spells.
You natural Rage loss over time, representing your Umbra Regeneration.
The delay before Umbra Regeneration restarts after gaining Rage. Rage Conservation is not triggered by spending Umbra or Rage.
The amount of Rage Points generated each time you hit an enemy.
The amount of Rage Points generated each time you are hit by an enemy.
Your basic Damage with equipped Weapons.
The global modifier applied to all Damage sources you inflict.
Physical Damage is the default Damage type for Weapons and have a natural chance to inflict Stun to their target.
Fire Damage have a natural chance to inflict Burn over time to their target.
Frost Damage have a natural chance to Freeze their target.
Lightning Damage have a natural chance to Shock their target.
Umbral Damage have a natural chance to inflict Frailty to their target.
Sacred Damage have a natural chance to inflict Weakness to their target.
Shadow Damage have a natural chance to Curse their target.
Rend Damage have a natural chance to inflict Bleed over time to their target.
Toxic Damage have a natural chance to inflict Poison over time to their target.
The global modifier to your Critical Chance with all weapons and spells.
The global modifier to your Critical Damage with all weapons and spells.
Your Critical Damage multiplier with Weapons. Represents the extra amount of Damage dealt by Critical Strikes.
Your Critical Chance with Weapons. Critical Strikes deal extra Damage and have a higher chance to inflict Status Ailments.
Your Critical Chance with Magic Spells. Critical Strikes deal extra Damage and have a higher chance to inflict Status Ailments.
Your Critical Damage multiplier with Magic Spells. Represents the extra amount of Damage dealt by Critical Strikes.
The global modifier to your Spells Cooldown. A lower Cooldown means that you will be able to cast Spells at a higher rate.
The global modifier to the Rage cost of all your Spells. Lower costs are not necessary a positive thing depending on your playstyle, since they lower the amount of the opposite Resource generated.
The global modifier to the Umbra cost of all your Spells. Lower costs are not necessary a positive thing depending on your playstyle, since they lower the amount of the opposite Resource generated.
The average Damage dealt by your Dash. The Dash uses the Damage of your equipped Weapons as its base value.
The maximum Range of your Dash. A higher Range means that you will be able to engage enemies from longer distances.
The amount of Rage Points generated for each enemy hit by your Dash.
The total Cooldown of your Dash.
The total Critical Chance of your Dash.
The total Critical Damage multiplier of your Dash.
Your total Thorns Damage. Thorns are Physical Damage inflicted to enemies when they hit you and which pierce through their Protections.
The global Damage modifier applied to your Thorns Damage.

The amount of Damage (points) which will ignore an enemy's Protection of a specific type. Piercing Attacks allow you to inflict partial Damage to the enemy's Health even if its Protections should normally prevent it.

The amount of Damage (percent) which will ignore an enemy's Protection of a specific type. Piercing Attacks allow you to inflict partial Damage to the enemy's Health even if its Protections should normally prevent it.
The amount of extra Damage inflicted to you enemy's Protection of a specific type. This amount of points will be inflicted to the Protections bars of an enemy regardless of the base Damage.

The amount of extra Damage inflicted to you enemy's Protection of a specific type. It will inflict to the Protections bars of an enemy an amount of Damage points equal to a percentage of its maximum size.
Your passive Resistances to a specific type of Damage. A negative Resistance means that you take more Damage of that type than usually.
The maximum amount of Stamina points available. Stamina points allow you to cast Movement-related Spells, such as the Dodgeroll.
The total delay for restoring one Stamina point that has been spent. A low value means that you'll recover your Stamina points quickly.
Your total Dodge Chance against all incoming attacks. Dodging attacks will completely ignore their effects, regardless of their type.

Your total Block Chance. Blocking an attack will reduce its effects based on your total Defense and will give you a temporary Defense boost. By default, you can only block Physical Attacks within your Block Angle. Block Chance is usually gained by equipping a Shield.
Your total Block Efficiency, representing the value of the temporary Defense boost obtained when blocking an attack. This bonus will quickly deplete with time.
Your total Block Angle. Attacks coming from the front and within this angle may be blocked depending on your total Block Chance, whereas Attacks from behind will never be blocked.
Your total Damage Reduction, which prevents a part of all incoming Damage, regardless of their source.
Your total Stun Resistance. May give you a chance to completely ignore an incoming Stun.
Your total Chance to inflict Burn with Fire Damage of any source.
Your total Chance to Freeze with Frost Damage.
The default duration of the Freeze you inflict if not specified by the source.
The global duration modifier applied to Freezing.
Your total Chance to Shock with Lightning Damage.
Your total Chance to Stun with Physical Damage.
The default duration of the Stun you inflict if not specified by the source.
The global duration modifier applied to Stunning.
Miscellaneous gameplay values which do not fall into one of the categories above.
The global modifier applied to your Chance of generating Corpses when killing enemies.
The total radius for automatically picking Globes around you.
The total radius for automatically picking Gold around you.
Your total Gold Find modifier. Increases the amount of looted Gold.
Your total Magic Find modifier. Increases the probability of looting Magic Items.
The global modifier to your Potions Cooldown. A lower Cooldown means that you will be able to use Potions and Phials at a higher rate.
The global modifier to your Potions Refill-time. A lower Refill-time means that your Potions and Phials will recover their charges faster.
The global modifier to your Potions Healing-capacity. A higher Healing-capacity means that your Healing Potions will be more efficient.
The global modifier to your Resistance against Magic Spells.
The global modifier to your Resistance against main Damage types.

The Fire Damage inflicted each time a Burn ticks. The first displayed value corresponds to one Burning stack whereas the second one represents the Damage for the maximum number of stacks you can put on one target.
The ticking delay used by a Burning stack for inflicting its Damage.
The default duration of the Burn you inflict if not specified by the source.
The global duration modifier applied to Burning.
The total Lightning Damage inflicted by a Shock.
The default duration of the Shock you inflict if not specified by the source.
The global duration modifier applied to Shocking.
Your total Chance to inflict Curse with Shadow Damage of any source.
The ticking delay used by a Cursing stack for propagating Status Ailments.

The Chance to propagate a Status Ailment stack each time a Curse ticks. The first displayed value corresponds to one Cursing stack whereas the second one represents the Chance for the maximum number of stacks you can put on one target.
The default duration of the Curse you inflict if not specified by the source.
The global duration modifier applied to Cursing.
The total Propagation Radius of the Curse you inflicts. Enemies within this range of the Cursed source are eligible targets for the propagation of Status Ailments.
The maximum amount of Status Ailments stacks that can be propagated by the Curse each time it ticks.
Your total Chance to inflict Bleed with Rend Damage of any source.
The ticking delay used by a Bleeding stack for inflicting its Damage.

The Rend Damage inflicted each time a Bleed ticks. The first displayed value corresponds to one Bleeding stack whereas the second one represents the Damage for the maximum number of stacks you can put on one target.
The default duration of the Bleed you inflict if not specified by the source.
The global duration modifier applied to Bleeding.
Your total Chance to inflict Weakness with Sacred Damage of any source.

The global Effiency of the Weakness you inflict, scaling up its different effects. The first displayed value corresponds to one Weakness stack whereas the second one represents the Effiency for the maximum number of stacks you can put on one target.
The default duration of the Weakness you inflict if not specified by the source.
The global duration modifier applied to Weakening.
Your total Chance to inflict Poison with Toxic Damage of any source.
The ticking delay used by a Poisoning stack for inflicting its Damage.

The Toxic Damage inflicted each time a Poison ticks. The first displayed value corresponds to one Poisoning stack whereas the second one represents the Damage for the maximum number of stacks you can put on one target.
The default duration of the Poison you inflict if not specified by the source.
The global duration modifier applied to Poisoning.
Your total Chance to inflict Frailty with Umbra Damage of any source.

The global Effiency of the Frailty you inflict, scaling up its different effects. The first displayed value corresponds to one Frailty stack whereas the second one represents the Effiency for the maximum number of stacks you can put on one target.
The default duration of the Frailty you inflict if not specified by the source.
The global duration modifier applied to Frailty.
The global duration modifier applied to Fear.
The global duration modifier applied to Frenzy.
The global duration modifier applied to Snare and Root.

The maximum number of stacks you can pile up on a unique target for each distinct Status Ailment. Most Status Ailments gain in power the more stacks you put on the same target, and they all have their independant stacks counter.

Your current Presence level. Affects how enemies spot and target you in combat. A normal value for Presence is 100%: below, you become harder to target and see. At 0%, you are invisible. At values higher than 100%, you are easier to spot and track.
Your basic Offensive capacities, representing your ability to attack and perform Damage.
Your basic Defensive capacities, representing your ability to reduce incoming Damage and avoid attacks.
Your Status Ailments capacities, representing your ability to inflict extra Damage and conditions over time.
Your Resource capacities, representing how you generate Resources of all kinds: Rage, Umbra and Stamina.

Your default Chance to perform an Overkill when killing an enemy with a specific Damage type. Overkills will give you a temporary Attack Speed boost, and their Chance increase the higher the Damage which induced the Death was.
Your Dash capacities, representing your ability to use the Dash effectively. The Dash is not available with all Weapons types and can be deactivated by clicking the Dash button on your HUD.
Your Potions capacities, representing your ability to use Potions and Phials effectively.
Your current Character level. All data from your Character Sheet which depend on a target level are displayed at your current level, but may vary against enemies from levels different from yours.
Your ability to use the Stun Ailment effectively. Stunning prevents targets from acting or moving for a short period of time.
Your ability to use the Burn Ailment effectively. Burning deals Fire Damage over time and can be stacked up to your maximum Ailments stacks number.

Your ability to use the Freeze Ailment effectively. Freezing prevents targets from acting or moving, and usually lasts longer than Stun but is environment-dependent: it can be interrupted by a Fire Damage or extended by the proximity of water. When unfreezing, a target will count as wet for a short period of time.

Your ability to use the Shock Ailment effectively. Shocking inflicts Lightning Damage to all enemies in a small area around your target and have a chance to Stun them. Unlike other Status Ailments, the Shock Damage is direct and not spread over time.

Your ability to use the Frailty Ailment effectively. Frailty reduces all the Damage dealt by the weakened target, its Stamina Regeneration and the efficiency of all the Protection Shattering it inflicts, making it less dangerous in combat. Frailty can be stacked up to your maximum Ailments stacks number.

Your ability to use the Weakness Ailment effectively. Weakness reduces all the Resistances of the target and damages its Protections over time while preventing them to regenerate, making it easier to kill. Weakness can be stacked up to your maximum Ailments stacks number.

Your ability to use the Curse Ailment effectively. Curse may propagate the target's Status Ailments to its nearby allies (expected the Curse itself). Curse can be stacked up to your maximum Ailments stacks number.
Your ability to use the Bleed Ailment effectively. Bleeding deals Rend Damage over time and can be stacked up to your maximum Ailments stacks number.
Your ability to use the Poison Ailment effectively. Poisoning deals Toxic Damage over time and can be stacked up to your maximum Ailments stacks number.

Your basic efficiency with main Damage types. Each Damage type can inflict its own Status Ailment type. A Damage can be comprised of several types, in which case it inherits from several independant Ailments Chance.
Your basic Resistances to main Damage types. A positive Resistance will negate part of all the Damage you will take from that type, depending on the Damage value and the source level.

Spells Damage is a special category representing Magic Spells sources (Spells which are not Weapon-based) and Staves attacks. It is complementary to your other Damage types and stacks with them in a case of a Spell which deal several types of Damage.

Your current Ferocity amount. The gauge represents your advancement on that attribute regarding the expected value at your level. If this attribute is labelled as "Weak" or "Average", then you should consider investing in it to improve your efficiency in combat.

Your current Toughness amount. The gauge represents your advancement on that attribute regarding the expected value at your level. If this attribute is labelled as "Weak" or "Average", then you should consider investing in it to improve your efficiency in combat.

Your current Agility amount. The gauge represents your advancement on that attribute regarding the expected value at your level. If this attribute is labelled as "Weak" or "Average", then you should consider investing in it to improve your efficiency in combat.

Your current Willpower amount. The gauge represents your advancement on that attribute regarding the expected value at your level. If this attribute is labelled as "Weak" or "Average", then you should consider investing in it to improve your efficiency in combat.
